          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2022-03-10 12:06:03" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>a congregation of Jews</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>synagogue</Gloss>
                <Gloss>congregation</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>Since the borrowed term ‘synagogue’ in receptor languages so frequently refers only to a building rather than to a congregation, it may be necessary in {S:04400900200018} to say ‘he asked for letters of introduction to leaders of the synagogues’ or ‘… leaders of the congregations of Jews.’</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
          </LEXSenses>
